    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Canopy-like arrangments of precious fabric, often consisting of celures, testers, and at least one set of valences. They were often used with chairs of estate, foot stools, and cushions, and could be raised onto a dais for added formality. For simple hangings of precious fabric placed behind a person, use "cloths of honor."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000048340/Hayward, Cloths of Estate, Furniture History (2005)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046892/Grove Art Online (2003-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vergelijkbaar met baldakijnen voor tronen of bedden. Troonhemels bestonden uit celures, hemels en ten minste één set met valletjes. Ze werden vaak gebruikt met speciale zetels, voetkrukjes en kussens, en konden voor extra formele gelegenheden op een podium worden geplaatst.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>與王座或寢具所使用之蓬罩類似，王室覆具包含天花板雕飾、床蓬罩以及至少一組的短窗幔。這些覆具常與王椅、腳凳及靠墊搭配使用，並可抬升至高臺處以增加其隆重性。該詞彙也可單指織物本身。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
